      "highlight": "\"You took your time,\" she says, not unkindly, but her voice is rough like gravel.",
      "full_response": "Ash sifts down from the soot-stained canvas roof, coating Mira\u2019s collar in gray. She leans against a spice stall, picking at a loose thread on her glove while she counts copper coins. The air smells of burnt cloves and wet wool.\n\nShe looks up as you approach. Her eyes lock onto the ledger bulging from your tunic.\n\n\"You took your time,\" she says, not unkindly, but her voice is rough like gravel. She taps the missing tip of her index finger against the table. \"The Council patrols doubled. They\u2019re smelling blood on the streets.\"\n\nShe glances toward the warehouse district, then back to you. \"And the guard?\""
